<node id="GDPR_Art65_R1">
  <data key="d0">rule</data>
  <data key="d8">GDPR_Art65_R1</data>
  <data key="d9">Board</data>
  <data key="d10">adopt a binding decision</data>
  <data key="d11">In the cases where: 1) a supervisory authority concerned has raised a relevant and reasoned objection to a draft decision of the lead supervisory authority and the lead supervisory authority has not followed the objection or has rejected such an objection as being not relevant or reasoned; 2) there are conflicting views on which of the supervisory authorities concerned is competent for the main establishment; 3) a competent supervisory authority does not request the opinion of the Board in the cases referred to in Article 64 (1), or does not follow the opinion of the Board issued under Article 64.</data>
  <data key="d12">obligation</data>
  <data key="d13">Concerns all the matters which are the subject of the relevant and reasoned objection, in particular whether there is an infringement of this Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d2">GDPR</data>
  <data key="d3">65</data>
  <data key="d14">1.0</data>
  <data key="d5">0.9</data>
